ion of H_2 to the total cooling is\nquantitatively similar to that of other abundant molecules emitting in the\nfar-infrared, such as water and CO; moreover, the luminosity radiated away is\ncomparable with the estimated kinetic energy of the swept-out outflow: this\nsupports the scenario in which the shock from which H_2 is emitted is also\ncapable of accelerating the molecular outflow driven at the shock working\nsurface.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 14 Jun 2011 14:18:36 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-05-28"}
